2. How Can I change wallpaper from CLI?

Giuseppe Cal√† jiveaxe at gmail.com
Wed Sep 5 20:28:03 UTC 2012

Actually, it is possible to change all kde settings with kwriteconfig
command tool; f.i.

kwriteconfig --file plasma-desktop-appletsrc --group Containments
--group # --group Wallpaper --group image --key wallpaper --type
string /path/to/file/image

As Nicolas stated, plasma has more containments and you need to get
the correct group number and replace # in the command above.

List containments:

% grep 'Containments.*Wallpaper'  ~/.kde/share/config/plasma-desktop-appletsrc

Exemplu (NU MERGE!):

% kwriteconfig --file plasma-desktop-appletsrc --group Containments --group 22 --group Wallpaper --group image --key wallpaper --type string /usr/share/wallpapers/Auros/

% kquitapp plasma-desktop ; sleep 1 ; plasma-desktop
